      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Divide and shape the <strong>beef mince</strong> into 3 <strong>meatballs </strong>per person (clean hands is the best way!)</p><p>Heat a large pot with a matching lid with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> beef meatballs</strong> and cook for 6-7 min, turning occasionally, until they're browned on all sides</p><p>Once browned, transfer to a plate and set aside, these will finish cooking in the sauce later (reserve the pot!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1604413553552-x200.jpg",
